<heading id="D08781E3A46AFFACFCD7FC8DFB54FCE6" bold="true" box="[801,1221,852,880]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFCD7FC8DFB54FCE6" bold="true" box="[801,1221,852,880]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">
II. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFCB4FC8DFC5BFCE6" box="[834,970,852,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Eumachia</taxonomicName>
in the Neotropics
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36A6504A46AFFACFCD7FC5BFAEFF9AC" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCF368FA46AFFACFCD7FC5BFA84FB4C" blockId="11.[801,1453,898,1594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFCD7FC5BFC16FC0C" box="[801,903,898,922]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFCD7FC5BFC16FC0C" box="[801,903,898,922]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 27 Neotropical species found from 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46AFFACFAADFC5BFA3AFC0C" box="[1371,1451,898,922]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and the Antilles to 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46AFFACFBF2FC7BFBFBFC2C" box="[1028,1130,930,954]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and Boliva. This genus was studied as 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFC78FC1BFB88FC4F" box="[910,1049,962,985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Margaritopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFC78FC1BFB88FC4F" box="[910,1049,962,985]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Margaritopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46AFFACFBCBFC1BFB4CFC4F" author="TAYLOR, C. M." box="[1085,1245,961,986]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFB10FC1BFBFBFC6C" authority="(DC.) Delprete &amp; J. H. Kirkbr." authorityName="Delprete &amp; J. H. Kirkbr." baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microdon">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFB10FC1BFA3AFC4C" box="[1254,1451,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia microdon</emphasis>
(DC.) Delprete &amp; J.H. Kirkbr.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFB85FC3BFA96FC6C" box="[1139,1287,994,1018]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cephalantha">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFB85FC3BFA96FC6C" box="[1139,1287,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">E. cephalantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFAB7FC3BFB3CFB8C" authority="(DC.) C. M. Taylor &amp; Razafim." authorityName="C. M. Taylor &amp; Razafim." baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaenotricha">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFAB7FC3BFCCAFB8C" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">E. chaenotricha</emphasis>
(DC.) C.M. Taylor &amp; Razafim.
</taxonomicName>
are the most commonly collected species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46AFFACFC11FBFBFB01FBAF" author="TAYLOR, C. M." box="[999,1168,1057,1082]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
separated three informal species groups, but these groups are not completely distinct and are not separated here. New nomenclatural combinations for some Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFBEFFB5BFB49FB0C" box="[1049,1240,1154,1178]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFBEFFB5BFB12FB0C" box="[1049,1155,1154,1178]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
were published by DELPRETE &amp; KIRKBRIDE (2015), who also lectotypified several names and updated the ranges of some species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCF368FA46AFFACFCB1FB3BFAEFF9AC" blockId="11.[801,1453,898,1594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">
Since the treatment by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46AFFACFBDAFB3BFB55FB6F" author="TAYLOR, C. M." box="[1068,1220,1249,1274]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, study has advanced on the species of eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46AFFACFC09FADBFBACFA8C" box="[1023,1085,1282,1306]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Accordingly 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFB3CFADBFCF1FAAC" baseAuthorityName="MULLER" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Mapouria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Chaenotrichae">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFB3CFADBFABDFA8F" box="[1226,1324,1282,1305]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Mapouria</emphasis>
ser. 
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFAAEFADBFCF1FAAC" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Chaenotrichae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFB8CFAFBFB4BFAAC" box="[1146,1242,1314,1338]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFB8CFAFBFB4BFAAC" box="[1146,1242,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the identities of three poorly known 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFC1BFA9BFBDFFACC" authorityName=", LACHENAUD" authorityYear="2013" box="[1005,1102,1346,1370]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFC1BFA9BFBDFFACC" box="[1005,1102,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Psychotria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
names are clarified here. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFABCFA9BFB98FAEC" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="depauperata">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFABCFA9BFC07FAEC" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Psychotria depauperata</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
is an older name for a previously known species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFC87FA5BFC61FA2C" authority="(Delprete &amp; E. B. Souza) C. M. Taylor &amp; E. B. Souza." authorityName="C. M. Taylor &amp; E. B. Souza." baseAuthorityName="Delprete &amp; E. B. Souza" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Margaritopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carrascoana">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFC87FA5BFBFBFA0F" box="[881,1130,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Margaritopsis carrascoana</emphasis>
(Delprete &amp; E.B. Souza) C.M. Taylor &amp; E.B. Souza.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFC05FA7BFABAFA2C" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." box="[1011,1323,1442,1466]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequifolia">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFC05FA7BFB51FA2C" box="[1011,1216,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Psychotria inaequifolia</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
represents an additional species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFC13FA1BFBD5FA4C" box="[997,1092,1474,1498]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFC13FA1BFBD5FA4C" box="[997,1092,1474,1498]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was not noted previously. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFA93FA1BFBB2FA6C" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schuechiana">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFA93FA1BFC25FA6C" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Psychotria schuechiana</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFADFFA3BFA3DFA6F" box="[1321,1452,1506,1529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Margaritopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFADFFA3BFA3DFA6F" box="[1321,1452,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Margaritopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46AFFACFCCBF9DBFC45F98F" author="TAYLOR, C. M." box="[829,980,1537,1562]" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, but further study shows that it does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFCCDF9FBFC0AF9AC" box="[827,923,1570,1594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFCCDF9FBFC0AF9AC" box="[827,923,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">Eumachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is not separable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46AFFACFB6DF9FBFAEFF9AC" authority="Mull. Arg." authorityName="Mull. Arg." box="[1179,1406,1570,1594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subtriflora">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46AFFACFB6DF9FBFA81F9AC" box="[1179,1296,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="300">P. subtriflora</emphasis>
Müll. Arg.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
